parameters: Sister Eleo: How are you today?

Clea: Actually, I would like to ask for your cooperation
with a request.

Sister Eleo: A-A dragon in Mount Monimos! It's hard to
believe all of a sudden... but it must be true, right?

Sister Eleo: So, what is it that you want my cooperation
with?

Clea: If possible, I would like to request the dispatch of
the priests.

Sister Eleo: That... is difficult. I cannot dispatch
comrades to a dangerous place where there is a dragon.

Sister Eleo: I am grateful for the help you have given us,
but I cannot put the lives of my comrades in danger...

Clea: I apologize for saying something that would trouble
you.

Sister Eleo: If it's just me as an individual, it's a
different story. I will participate as a friend, not as a
member of the church!

Priestess Sophia: Eleo-chan... You don't have to push
yourself, okay?

Priestess Sophia: I'm sorry. It's because I said I would
come.

Sister Eleo: I-If that's the case, even more so! It can't
be helped, right, Sophia-san?

Sister Eleo: I can't send everyone back empty-handed after
they came all this way!

Sister Eleo: ...If there is anything I can do to be of help
for Sophia-san.

Priestess Sophia: I would like to ask for your help as
well, Eleo-chan. Is it okay for you to come?

Clea: Of course, it would be helpful to have more people
who can heal.

Sister Eleo: Please leave it to me. I will definitely be of
help to everyone.
Clea: What should we do next?

Mage Relm: I think it will be difficult to gather more
collaborators without a specific plan.

Mage Relm: Why don't we go back to the Adventurer's Guild
once?
Thief Nora: Ah, I also think that would be a good idea!
Clea: Let's do that. There might have been some progress.

Sister Eleo: Dragon extermination... Ah... What should we
do!

Sister Eleo: If you have any troubles, please feel free to
reach out to me at any time.
Sister Eleo: Who might you be?
Clea: I've come from the Adventurer's Guild.

Sister Eleo: Thank you very much! Finally, the goddess of
salvation has arrived!

Sister Eleo: The request is simple. We would like to ask
for the reformation of a certain priest.

Sister Eleo: It means living in accordance with the
teachings of Terios, the state religion!

Mage Relm: Hmph, it seems like a typical religious person's
way of thinking. I wish they would consider things more
logically.

Sister Eleo: That crescent moon... Are you a mage from the
Academy?

Mage Relm: Yes, I am a mage from the Magic Academy. I'm
different from those priests who don't create anything, you
know.

Sister Eleo: Seeing you, who have been excommunicated from
the church, I can understand the reason behind it.
Mage Relm: Where did you see this genius?!
Sister Eleo: That arrogant attitude of yours!
Thief Nora: Oh, please calm down!

Sister Eleo: Ugh, I apologize. First, please get to know
her behavior.

Sister Eleo: I am at the neighboring church, so please take
care of me.
Clea: So, what is her name?

Sister Eleo: Her name is Sister Sophia. She is the biggest
troublemaker in the history of the village.
Sister Eleo: Did everyone talk about dragons?
Clea: Yes, I explained it as part of the conversation.

Sister Eleo: ...It was over two years ago, Sophia-san
collapsed in front of the church.
Sister Eleo: No, I was just drunk.

Sister Eleo: But, the words from that time shouldn't have
been a lie...

Sister Eleo: It's fine for you to leave here, but going to
search for a dragon...?

Sister Eleo: I didn't want to hear such lies. I'd rather
you tell me that you hate me--
Mage Relm: W-Wait, what are you doing!?

Clea: Sophia-san believed me without laughing or looking,
even with the wound inflicted by the dragon.

Clea: Please, Sister Eleo, lend us the power of Sophia-
san.
Sister Eleo: First, please put on some clothes.

Thief Nora: You can't just suddenly take off your clothes,
you know~!
Sister Eleo: Is it true that Sophia-san didn't laugh?

Mage Relm: Yes, it's true. Or do you not believe in the
words of a mage?

Sister Eleo: No... I will choose to believe. I believe that
Sophia-san has her reasons.

Sister Eleo: Let's go to the church to say goodbye to
Sophia-san.
Mischievous boy: 'Ahaha, we have a guest!'
Mischievous boy: 'The boob ghost has appeared!'
Mischievous boy: Ahaha, we have a guest!
......If we trouble Eleo-san, it won't end well.

Energetic Boy: I want to play in the meadow, but there are
too many dangerous people, so it's not allowed!

Energetic boy: Big sister Sophia! Will you play with me
again?

Energetic Boy: I want to play in the grasslands, but there
are too many dangerous people, so it's not allowed!
Orphanage Grandma: Ahaha, it's a lively place, isn't it?

Orphanage Granny: You need to cut back on alcohol! You
can't keep relying on Eleo forever!

Orphanage Granny: What's this? So the rundown shop is
finally opening!

Orphanage Granny: So that guy's father can finally make a
living. But it's quite something to be able to persuade that
stubborn person.
Priestess Sophia: Oh no, no. It's thanks to them.

Orphanage Granny: Sophia, you've become a little more
cheerful, haven't you?

Orphanage Granny: When you came here, your face was like
that of a dead person. But now, except in front of Eleo, you
have a sad expression.

Orphanage Granny: You, who don't show gratitude to them,
are starting to have the face of a priestess.

Orphanage Granny: Hmph, just because of that, it doesn't
mean you can drink too much! Even though you're an adult,
you still have a spoiled side to you.
Priestess Sophia: Hehe, I will be careful, don't worry.

Orphanage Granny: However, I'll allow it just for today. Go
and call out to everyone in the village!
Orphanage Grandma: Ahaha, it's a lively place, isn't it?

Orphanage Granny: You should cut back on alcohol! You can't
keep relying on Eleo forever!
Clea: It seems to be sealed with some special power.
Please wake up already, wake up properly.
Please wake up already, wake up properly!
Clea: Huh!? Where are we, exactly!?

Sister Eleo: I was really worried, you know! When I heard
that the nun had collapsed, I hurriedly went to fetch her.

Sister Eleo: I thought Sophia-san had passed out from
drinking, but I never expected Clea-san and the others to
collapse as well.
Sister Eleo: What happened at the campus?

Clea: I was there at the turning point of things. I believe
that person will definitely take a new step forward.

Sister Eleo: That's wonderful! Although I don't know who
they are, may they receive the blessings of Imiserinos.

Clea: I apologize for causing trouble. I will wake everyone
up and go back now--

Clea (To my dear friends, this is a small token of my
gratitude. Please make use of it.)

Clea (I believe that you all can make use of this as proof
that the Phantom Thief Perno has truly ceased to exist.)

Clea (And... if you ever find yourself in trouble, please
be sure to contact me. There may be little I can do right
now, but I will definitely come to your aid.)
Clea: Hehe, let's go wake everyone up.
